Do you feel stressed
Yes, I do feel stressed sometimes, especially when facing tight deadlines or challenging tasks. However, I see stress as a normal part of work, and I try to manage it effectively by staying organized, prioritizing my tasks, and maintaining a positive mindset.


How do you handle stress
I handle stress in several ways. First, I try to maintain a positive mindset, as it helps me stay focused and approach problems more effectively. I also prioritize my tasks based on urgency and importance, which allows me to manage my time more efficiently.

In addition, I make it a habit to plan ahead at the end of each week so I have a clear understanding of what needs to be done. This helps me anticipate potential challenges and prepare for them in advance.

Finally, I believe maintaining a healthy lifestyle plays an important role in managing stress. Staying physically active and taking time to relax helps me stay calm and think clearly, so I can handle pressure more effectively when it arises.

Does listening to music make you feel relaxed
Yes, definitely. Listening to music is my go-to way to relax whenever I need some downtime. It's a great way to switch off and clear my mind after a busy day.
Personally, I enjoy calm genres like acoustic or lo-fi beats, as they help me feel more at ease and focused.

What kinds of places or environments would make you feel relaxed
I feel most relaxed in quiet and peaceful environments, such as a park or a cozy cafe. Being surrounded by green spaces or a calm atmosphere helps me clear my mind and recharge.
I find that these environments allow me to slow down, reduce stress, and regain focus.
